article.headline: Robert Morris 20, Monmouth, N.J. 17
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- A Michael Walser field goal with 47 seconds left on the clock lifted Robert Morris to a 20-17 victory over Monmouth on Saturday. The Hawks (0-2) had initially led 14-0 after junior running back David Sinisi rushed for two touchdowns in the first quarter. But Monmouth then saw its lead evaporate to Robert Morris (1-1). First there was Erik Cwalinski's 43-yard touchdown pass to Julian Ellison in the second quarter. Robert Morris freshman running back Jeff Link then ran for 3 yards to tie the game in the third quarter. The game then turned into a duel of kickers. Walser, a junior, put Robert Morris in the lead in the third quarter with a field goal from 22. Monmouth senior kicker Fred Weingart responded in the fourth quarter with a field goal from 42. But Walser then made his final field goal from 36 to win the game for the Colonials.
